quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  7,100,"Does it not dawn upon those who inherited the earth after its [former] inhabitants that if We wish We will punish them for their sins, and set a seal on their hearts so they would not hear"
  7,101,"These are the towns some of whose accounts We recount to you. Their apostles certainly brought them manifest proofs, but they were not the ones to believe in what they had denied earlier. Thus does Allah put a seal on the hearts of the faithless"
  7,102,"We did not find in most of them any [loyalty to] covenants. Indeed, We found most of them to be transgressors"
  7,103,"Then after them We sent Moses with Our signs to Pharaoh and his elite, but they wronged them. So observe how was the fate of the agents of corruption"
  7,104,"And Moses said, ‘O Pharaoh, I am indeed an apostle from the Lord of all the worlds"
  7,105,It behooves me to say nothing about Allah except the truth. I certainly bring you a manifest proof from your Lord. So let the Children of Israel go with me.’
  7,106,"He said, ‘If you have brought a sign, produce it, should you be truthful.’"
  7,107,"Thereat he threw down his staff, and behold, it became a manifest python"
  7,108,"Then he drew out his hand, and behold, it was white to the onlookers"